  "text": "To illustrate these types of non-linear effects from the regression results, the regression result in the national sector is used. The turning point in the national sector is identified as GDP* = US$ 1,127, indicating the threshold value below which GDP t is negatively associated with a national ECI t and above which GDP t is positively associated with a national ECI t . More specifically, this result implies that, if Pakistan does not improve the supply side of power generation, such as CU t or TNTPR t , the demand for oil and gas will be greater than the demand for electricity, as GDP t exceeds the threshold value of the turning point. This is because people will be using these inputs to meet the demand for electricity by using backup generators. This result is another confirmation of the findings of [CITATION_1] in that there will be a huge energy shortfall in Pakistan without an improvement in the power-supply systems.",
